{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"78009ac8-a705-4d7d-b645-22dc963c09be","content":"The issue is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference modules defined in files listed **above** them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but is listed first.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_9XmMnGvWqQedNdn87FObOV","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-6e04b0d6c5b04105a848f61aed0f2921/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-6e04b0d6c5b04105a848f61aed0f2921/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"5cb23f24-4459-4820-a42c-1a36ae6d4457","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order in the `.fsproj` matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed *above* them. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. Services.fs — depends on Domain.fs (opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`)\n2. Domain.fs — defines the types\n3. Program.fs — depends on both\n\n`Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`. This won't work because in F#, a file can only reference things defined in files that appear earlier in the compilation order.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n\n\n1. Domain.fs (defines types)\n2. Services.fs (uses Domain types)\n3. Program.fs (uses both)","outputTokens":472,"requestId":"1C51:2ED258:B3DC49:D09F89:69F3FA0D"},"id":"c6c1aa68-24c1-4c0a-88eb-22fe67aac178","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00:55:50.522Z","parentId":"df5ab042-64ab-465a-ae03-7b983411cf37"}
